<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code computes FormatLen1/FormatLen2 using strlen() or memchr() to locate the terminating '\0' (e.g. when String1Max == UTASSERT_STRINGBUF_NULL_TERM it uses strlen(String1)), and then calls memcmp(String1, String2, FormatLen1) to compare the character content. This is using memcmp to compare null-terminated strings (or prefixes determined from null terminators), which violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.14.
</scenario>

